Art. 11 determines that, the data controller or data processor must adopt the necessary technical and organisational measures to ensure the security of the personal data processed, ensuring their preservation and avoiding their alteration, loss, unauthorised processing or access. In this sense, personal data must not be recorded in files, systems or processing centres that do not meet the security conditions for the integrity, confidentiality and guarantee of the same.Last modified 10 Jan 2022
				
			